wants us to find two days
we can set aside

01:32.920 --> 01:34.160
so they can send
a fellow down here

01:34.160 --> 01:36.440
to teach us all this new
barcode system they've got

01:36.440 --> 01:38.000
for arrest paperwork

01:38.280 --> 01:40.760
for cross-jurisdictional
and inter-departmental cases.

01:41.160 --> 01:42.320
Two days?

01:42.520 --> 01:43.560
For barcodes?

01:46.440 --> 01:48.920
A most unusual story out
of the Southwest today...

01:49.040 --> 01:51.520
after making what city
dispatchers assumed would be

01:51.520 --> 01:52.280
a routine call to a house...

01:52.280 --> 01:53.720
Sir, they're waiting for me
to call them back

01:53.720 --> 01:56.200
...in the eastern suburbs
of Phoenix, Arizona.
with those dates.

01:56.200 --> 01:57.960
Two Emergency Medical
Technicians

01:57.960 --> 02:00.320
and their vehicle appear
to have vanished.

02:00.320 --> 02:01.760
The District Attorney of Phoenix

02:01.760 --> 02:02.840
had this to say.

02:02.920 --> 02:05.120
I'd like to emphasize
that while we are vigorously

02:05.120 --> 02:07.720
investigating the disappearance
of these men and their vehicle,

02:07.720 --> 02:10.199
at the present time
there is no definitive proof

02:10.199 --> 02:12.440
that they've actually met
with foul play.

02:12.440 --> 02:13.760
That having been said...

02:13.760 --> 02:15.320
Do you remember that lady?

02:16.160 --> 02:18.080
Said she dreamt things?

02:20.000 --> 02:21.040
From Phoenix.

02:23.560 --> 02:24.800
You get me her number.

